# Cloudflare Pages rewrites for generated artifacts composed by
# .github/workflows/cloudflare-pages.yml.
#
# The deploy workflow removes DocC's per-symbol HTML shell copies to keep the
# artifact below Pages' file-count limit. The DocC app is a JavaScript shell
# backed by /docs/data/, so direct links can route through the single shell.
#
# Destination is `/docs/` (canonical directory form) rather than
# `/docs/index.html`. Pages canonicalizes asset URLs ending in `/index.html`
# to their directory equivalent — so a 200 rewrite to `/docs/index.html`
# silently fails to resolve and the request falls through to the project's
# homepage fallback. Cloudflare Pages does not support Netlify's `200!`
# force flag, only plain status codes.
#
# Probe rule (delete after verifying _redirects deploys correctly):
# /__redirects-probe must rewrite to a known JSON asset so we can confirm
# _redirects is being applied on production.
/__redirects-probe /docs/data/documentation/swifttui.json 200
/docs/documentation /docs/ 200
/docs/documentation/* /docs/ 200
